Charlie will inherit a large chocolate factory. He does not yet have the skills to runt he factory himself, and will need help in its management for a few years.
Staff will assist Charlie in paying bills on time and will help to hire a manager to assist him in the day to day activities.
Charlie cannot open a locked door, which puts him at risk in case of an emergency (fire, etc.).
Charlie is not to be left unattended and is not allowed to be locked in a room by himself. All locks have been removed from interior doors in his home.
Charlie will practice effective business management
Charlie will work on taking charge for longer periods of time.
Charlie will check on the staff fewer than 4 times each shift. He is learning to trust them to operate the factory on their own.
Charlie will yell at the staff fewer than 3 times each hour for the next 12 weeks.
Charlie will improve his computer skills and learn to type 50 words per minute Independently.
Charlie will learn to dress appropriately for the office by choosing his suit and ironing his shirts with fewer than 2 verbal prompts.
